    course_description = '<section class="content-box read-more" data-nav-section="Course_overview" id="course-overview"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Course overview</p> <p>Create the smart software and systems of the future by studying Deakin’s Bachelor of Software Engineering (Honours). This course arms you with the skills needed to build disruptive technologies that create change, making you a sought-after expert ready to solve tomorrow’s business problems through creative computing solutions. Explore a broad range of exciting study areas, including robotics, algorithms, programming and software architecture, and apply your skills in world-class facilities.<br/><br/>Gain practical experience and learn how to work successfully in a team with project-based learning activities. Contribute to real-world projects alongside professional engineers during industry placements. You will develop specialised skills in robotics, cyber-physical systems and the Internet-of-Things (IoT), all while getting hands-on with the latest software engineering tools that allow you to push beyond the limitations of traditional technologies.<br/><br/><strong>Want to be at the forefront of robotics, computing and smart technologies?</strong></p><div style="display: none; transition: max-height 0.8s, opacity 0.8s; overflow: hidden; max-height: 0px; opacity: 0;"> <p>The rapid advancement of sensing hardware, computers and smart devices has created growing demand for software engineers who can develop complex systems that meet the need for smart and innovative technologies. From Mars rovers to smart homes and cities, robotic surgery and precision agriculture, software engineers combine software systems and embedded hardware to create solutions that benefit society. With a degree from Victoria ’s #1 university for graduate employment, you will be prepared to meet this demand and thrive in a fast-evolving industry.</p> <p>Your ideas and creativity will flourish in our state-of-the-art facilities. You will work alongside hardware designers and app developers to drive the development of computing solutions that interact with people, environments and other technologies.</p> <p>This course focuses on the development of skills in systems development and management, programming, software development, embedded systems development, systems integration and build, and software design.</p> </div><a class="sup uppercase" href="#" style="display: block; margin-top: 10px;">Read more</a></section>',
